s previously he served as deutsche bank’s chief actuary for all life financing transactions prior to his time on wall street bob was the life insurance structured financing solutions practice leader at towers wyatt now willis towers watson consulting life insurers reinsurers and banks on numerous capital management and insurancerelated activities bob’s reinsurance experience includes founding annuity and life re in bermuda as chief underwriter and chief operating officer and was instrumental in their successful 3 million public launch at swiss re bob was head of actuarial marketing for us life reinsurance operations bob was also president of two companies within swiss re and served on the board of directors for rgaswiss financial bob graduated from fordham university in with a bachelor of arts degree in mathematics he is a fellow of the society of actuaries a member of the american academy of actuaries brian holland chief marketing officer brian was senior vice president of the life solutions group at willis re a team responsible for building willis re’s entry into the life and annuity reinsurance market as principal in the advisory firm mann conroy eisenberg  associates brian created risk management and securitization solutions for insurers reinsurers banks and large benefit plans brian served as executive vice president and member of the board of directors at annuity  life re america developing the new us life reinsurance operations brian was vice president domestic and international risk management at ing re serving as global chief marketing officer he also developed ing re’s entry into the bermuda and japan markets brian also held senior marketing and underwriting positions at transamerica re and general re he received his bachelor of science degree in business management marketing from providence college   steeve jean chief financial officer steeve was most recently a principal with kpmg he has over  years of experience in the insurance industry working with international insurance groups and big four firms at kpmg steeve assisted companies with international accounting standards reinsurance transactions mergers and acquisitions actuarial system implementations stress testing and financial statement conversions prior to kpmg steeve was a vicepresident at transamerica where his responsibilities included financial reporting capital management acquisitions and reinsurance with financial oversight over international operations at old mutual steeve led a team responsible for both us and bermuda financial reporting steeve spent several years at ernst  young where he led the delivery of large advisory projects steeve began his career with metlife’s canadian operations with a focus on financial management for both the group and individual life divisions steeve is a fellow of the society of actuaries a fellow of the canadian institute of actuaries and a member of the american academy of actuaries he obtained is bachelor’s degree in applied mathematics from the university of sherbrooke” stephen gallant chief investment officer prior to cofounding somerset re stephen was head of rates for ing investment management’s proprietary fixed income group stephen served on the group’s executive team which oversaw the firm’s 8 billion portfolio he was directly responsible for all interest rate sensitive products including the highly successful mortgage derivative strategy which was one of the largest such strategies in the us stephen also helped develop an offshore trust for ing japan and managed a holding company opportunity fund prior to his role at ing stephen spent 4 years in fixed income trading where he traded corporate bonds preferred stocks and mortgagebacked securities stephen was a founder and comanager of portage equity investments i and ii an earlystage venture capital fund stephen currently is a member of the investment committee for the clemson university foundation stephen is a member of the cfa institute where he holds the chartered financial analyst designation he received a bachelor of science degree in finance from washington university in st louis tom conroy chief administrative and compliance officer as managing partner at mann conroy eisenberg  assoc tom led the team that conceptualized developed and obtained patents on financial derivatives for transferring mortality and longevity risk to the capital markets and for a method to maximize the value of corporate life insurance programs as president of ing reinsurance tom led the unit from a midsized us life reinsurance operation to  market share in north america as president of ing institutional markets he created a business producing consistent earnings growth tom also served as chief financial officer at ing’s security life of denver and built the firm’s investment unit as cfo and a director of teton energy tom built the financial unit as they moved from the vancouver stock exchange to a us registration as a director he chaired the audit committee and the nominating  governance committee tom began his career at ernst  ernst now ernst  young where he helped to developed their first audit software package tom is a retired captain in the us army reserve he earned an mba mathematical models and computer sciences from the university of chicago and a bachelor of science degree accounting from depaul university tom is a member of the american institute of certified public accountants gerald wigger managing director – investments gerald was formerly head of financial engineering risk systems at zuercher kantonalbank his team was responsible for risk modeling and supervision of all trading books reporting to the supervisory board and liaising with the swiss regulator as head of pricing at axa winterthur gerald and his actuarial team were responsible for new business pricing deal approvals and inforce liability management for the traditional life business gerald also developed hedging strategies for the variable annuity business in collaboration with his peers gerald launched an award winning new life insurance product prior gerald was vice president at bank of america merrill lynch in london responsible for the valuation of fixed income structured products at lucht probst and associates in frankfurt gerald was senior quantitative analyst working on structured products analytics gerald holds a masters and a phd in physics from the eth zurich and a bachelor of science from the university of cape town gerald did his postdoctoral research at the geballe laboratory at stanford university scott selkirk managing director – pricing scott was previously the head of pricing at standard life of canada’s bermuda branch where he led the evaluation of all new reinsurance opportunities and was responsible for client relationship management as vice president at ace tempest life re scott was involved in all aspects of new business including pricing client relations and treaty negotiation covering both variable annuity guarantee and traditional life reinsurance solutions prior to relocating to bermuda in 7 scott worked for new york life ing and metlife where he held various actuarial roles mainly focused on product development where he worked closely with distribution teams to bring innovative and sophisticated life insurance solutions to market scott is a fellow of the society of actuaries and a member of the american academy of actuaries scott graduated with a bachelor of arts degree in statistics from boston university   somerset re ltd bermuda office     woodbourne avenue pembroke hm  bermuda   patrick kelleher chief executive officer pkellehersomersetrecom brian holland chief marketing officer bhollandsomersetrecom robert reale chief actuary  chief underwriting officer brealesomersetrecom steeve jean chief financial officer sjeansomersetrecom scott selkirk managing director – pricing sselkirksomersetrecom   somerset re ltd swiss branch   dufourstrasse  8 zurich switzerland   thomas conroy chief administrative  com