al and traditional markets by evaluating your specific needs we tailormake the most appropriate product and customize it to fit efficiently into your portfolio for all the following classes of business cover can be arranged on a treaty proportional or nonproportional basis including exposure or reciprocity arrangements swaps industry loss warranty including live and dead catastrophe and replicat agriculturecrop proportional and stop loss aviation airline general aviation and speciality aviation​ marine ocean and inland including hull yachts cargo liability and offshore energy property us europe japan and specific territories farm mutuals and smaller regional companies weather temperature rainfall snowfall humidity solar radiation wind speed and weatherdriven commodity businesses interested get in touch somerset holdings  history somerset holdings history founded by john brooks somerset holdings ltd shl is a bermuda based reinsurance intermediary regulated by the bermuda money authority bma shl’s position as an independent intermediary domiciled in bermuda places it on the doorstep of the most dynamic reinsurance marketplace in the world our relationships with intermediaries and underwriters in the key insurance markets of the uk and united states give us extensive reach and breadth john brooks has over 4 years of experience in the london market including setting up a lloyd’s broker in  the lloyds broker originally started out handling predominately marine reinsurance however the company quickly developed into a multiclass broking house handling property aviation airline and ga as well as marine in 3 the company was acquired by hrh a large us broker at the time john remained a director of the company until his departure in december 7 somerset holdings ltd was formed in  and approved by the bma during late  see our products somerset reinsurance ltd completes  million capital raise please click here if you are not redirected within a few seconds   deutsch español suomi